<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="518" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/5–1754: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_TOMLINSONWM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tomlinson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d518fn1">Repeated for information to Bonn and
                                London.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-17T21:00:00+01:00">May 17,
                                    1954—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <gloss target="#t_Coled1">Coled</gloss> 244. Department pass <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_ALPHANDH1">Alphand</persName> states government will not
                            bring question of fixing date for <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>
                            debate for Committee of Presidents tomorrow and will oppose fixing date
                            if question is raised on grounds prior conditions of Saar and protocol
                            signature are not fulfilled.</p>
                        <p>Intentions now are to wait until after extraordinary Socialist Congress
                            is held before asking committee to fix debate. In this way Socialists
                            will be under discipline in committee and in Parliament in setting date.
                            According to <persName corresp="#p_ALPHANDH1">Alphand</persName>,
                            procedures have approval of <persName corresp="#p_MOLLETG1">Mollet</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_TEITGENPH1">Teitgen</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_ALPHANDH1">Alphand</persName> mentioned around June 15 or June 20 as possible
                            dates for debate assuming Government does not fall and Indochina
                            situation does not deteriorate.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_TOMLINSONWM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tomlinson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>